Probability of head = 3/5
Probability of tail = 2/5
Total tosses n = 5
Using Binomial expansion we know that : nCx px qn-x

a) All head Means x = 5
nCx px qn-x 
5C5 (3/5)5 (2/5)5-5
= 243 / 3125

b) AT LEAST 3 HEAD  
P(3 heads) + P(4 heads) + P(5 heads)
nCx px qn-x =>  5C3 (3/5)3 (2/5)5-3 + 5C4 (3/5)4 (2/5)5-4 + 5C5 (3/5)5 (2/5)5-5  
= 10 * 27 * 4 / 55 + 5 * 81 * 2 / 55 + 243 / 55
= 1080 + 810 + 243 / 3125
= 2133 / 3125

c) At most 1 head
= 5C1 (3/5)1 (2/5)5-1
= 240 / 3125

